===Etymology===
{{OF.}} ''parer'' "arrange, prepare, trim," from {{L.}} parare "make ready," from Proto-Indo-European base ''*per-'' "to bring forward, bring forth".

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: pâr
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /peə(r)/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /pe@(r)/

==== Homophones ====
*[[pair]]
*[[pear]]
==== Wry definition ====
* A [[trio]] of [[pear]]s [[pare]]d to a [[pair]] of [[pear]]s.

===Transitive verb===
'''to pare''' ([[pared]], pared)
#to [[remove]] the [[outer]] [[covering]] or [[skin]] of something with a [[knife]]
#to [[reduce]] or [[trim]] something as if by cutting off

